[[Kyrgyzstan]] had a total primary energy supply ([[TPES]]) of 4.13 [[tonne of oil equivalent|Mtoe]] in 2012.<ref name=iea2012 /> Electricity consumption was 10.14 [[TWh]]. The majority of primary energy came from fossil fuels, with coal (25%) and oil products (38%) the main sources. [[Hydroelectricity]], the only significant renewable source in the country, accounted for 8.6% of the primary energy supply and almost all of the electricity supply.<ref name=iea2012>{{cite web|title=Kyrgyzstan|url=http://www.iea.org/statistics/statisticssearch/report/?year=2012&country=Kyrgyzstan&product=Balances|website=www.iea.org|publisher=International Energy Agency (IEA)|accessdate=5 October 2015}}</ref>

