{{see also|List of Dungeons & Dragons monsters}} {{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Dungeons & Dragons'' 4th edition monsters}} '''''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' 4th edition''' (see [[editions of Dungeons & Dragons|editions of ''Dungeons & Dragons'']]) was released in 2008. The first book containing monsters to be published was the Heroic Tier adventure ''[[Keep on the Shadowfell]]'', followed closely with the release of the first set of "core" rulebooks.
==WTC 21718 – ''Keep on the Shadowfell'' (2008)== '''''Keep on the Shadowfell''''' is the first official product from the 4th edition ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' line.<ref name=InfoFromWotC>{{cite web| url=http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/4spo/20080507a|title= Keep on the Shadowfell Spotlight Interview|publisher=Wizards of the Coast|accessdate=2009-01-16}} </ref> It is part one of a three part series of [[Adventure (role-playing games)|adventures]]. The monsters appear in the 80-page adventure book booklet and are organized as they appear in the adventure encounters.
